messageHandlers.script:
# implement your handler here
	system.perspective.print("Table to excel ")
	
	rowIndicesTimeWise = {}
	rowIndicesTimeWise['7:00A'] = 0
	rowIndicesTimeWise['7:30A'] = 1
	rowIndicesTimeWise['8:00A'] = 2
	rowIndicesTimeWise['9:00A'] = 3
	rowIndicesTimeWise['10:30A'] = 4
	rowIndicesTimeWise['1:15P'] = 5
	rowIndicesTimeWise['2:30P(GH)'] = 6
	rowIndicesTimeWise['3:30P(GH)'] = 7
	rowIndicesTimeWise['GH Evening'] = 8
	
	## define event-name category dict
	eventCategoryDict = {}
	## get category - eventname list
	categoriesData = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/GetEventCategoriesList")
	if categoriesData is not None and categoriesData.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(categoriesData.getRowCount()):
			eventName = categoriesData.getValueAt(i,'eventName')
			if eventName is not None:
				eventName = eventName.strip()
				categoryName = categoriesData.getValueAt(i,'categoryName')
				eventCategoryDict[eventName] = categoryName
#	system.perspective.print(eventCategoryDict)
	#get notes data for each day
	parameters  = {"date":self.view.custom.DayList[0]}
	table1Notes = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/Get_WeeklyScheduleNote_PerLocationAndTime", parameters)
	
	parameters  = {"date":self.view.custom.DayList[1]}
	table2Notes = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/Get_WeeklyScheduleNote_PerLocationAndTime", parameters)

	parameters  = {"date":self.view.custom.DayList[2]}
	table3Notes = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/Get_WeeklyScheduleNote_PerLocationAndTime", parameters)
	
	parameters  = {"date":self.view.custom.DayList[3]}
	table4Notes = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/Get_WeeklyScheduleNote_PerLocationAndTime", parameters)

	parameters  = {"date":self.view.custom.DayList[4]}
	table5Notes = system.db.runNamedQuery("Event/ParticipantEvents/WeeklySchedule/Get_WeeklyScheduleNote_PerLocationAndTime", parameters)
	
	table1Data = self.getChild("FlexContainer").getChild("Table_1").custom.tableData
	table2Data = self.getChild("FlexContainer").getChild("Table_2").custom.tableData
	table3Data = self.getChild("FlexContainer").getChild("Table_3").custom.tableData
	table4Data = self.getChild("FlexContainer").getChild("Table_4").custom.tableData
	table5Data = self.getChild("FlexContainer").getChild("Table_5").custom.tableData
	
	## merge notes data with main data
	## First table that is Monday
	if table1Notes is not None and table1Notes.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(table1Notes.getRowCount()):
			timeVal = table1Notes.getValueAt(i,'TIME')
			locName = table1Notes.getValueAt(i,'location')
			note = table1Notes.getValueAt(i,'note')
			if note != None and note != "":
				## add to respective dataset
				rowIndexToModify = rowIndicesTimeWise[timeVal]
				originalValue = table1Data.getValueAt(rowIndexToModify,locName)
				newValue = "Note: " + str(note) + ";" + originalValue
				table1Data = system.dataset.setValue(table1Data, rowIndexToModify, locName, newValue)
	## Second table that is Tuesday
	if table2Notes is not None and table2Notes.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(table2Notes.getRowCount()):
			timeVal = table2Notes.getValueAt(i,'TIME')
			locName = table2Notes.getValueAt(i,'location')
			note = table2Notes.getValueAt(i,'note')
			if note != None and note != "":
				## add to respective dataset
				rowIndexToModify = rowIndicesTimeWise[timeVal]
				originalValue = table2Data.getValueAt(rowIndexToModify,locName)
				newValue = "Note: " + str(note) + ";" + originalValue
				table2Data = system.dataset.setValue(table2Data, rowIndexToModify, locName, newValue)
	## Third table that is Wednesday
	if table3Notes is not None and table3Notes.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(table3Notes.getRowCount()):
			timeVal = table3Notes.getValueAt(i,'TIME')
			locName = table3Notes.getValueAt(i,'location')
			note = table3Notes.getValueAt(i,'note')
			if note != None and note != "":
				## add to respective dataset
				rowIndexToModify = rowIndicesTimeWise[timeVal]
				originalValue = table3Data.getValueAt(rowIndexToModify,locName)
				newValue = "Note: " + str(note) + ";" + originalValue
				table3Data = system.dataset.setValue(table3Data, rowIndexToModify, locName, newValue)
	## Fourth table that is Thursday
	if table4Notes is not None and table4Notes.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(table4Notes.getRowCount()):
			timeVal = table4Notes.getValueAt(i,'TIME')
			locName = table4Notes.getValueAt(i,'location')
			note = table4Notes.getValueAt(i,'note')
			if note != None and note != "":
				## add to respective dataset
				rowIndexToModify = rowIndicesTimeWise[timeVal]
				originalValue = table4Data.getValueAt(rowIndexToModify,locName)
				newValue = "Note: " + str(note) + ";" + originalValue
				table4Data = system.dataset.setValue(table4Data, rowIndexToModify, locName, newValue)

	## Fifth table that is Friday
	if table5Notes is not None and table5Notes.getRowCount() > 0:
		for i in range(table5Notes.getRowCount()):
			timeVal = table5Notes.getValueAt(i,'TIME')
			locName = table5Notes.getValueAt(i,'location')
			note = table5Notes.getValueAt(i,'note')
			if note != None and note != "":
				## add to respective dataset
				rowIndexToModify = rowIndicesTimeWise[timeVal]
				originalValue = table5Data.getValueAt(rowIndexToModify,locName)
				newValue = "Note: " + str(note) + ";" + originalValue
				table5Data = system.dataset.setValue(table5Data, rowIndexToModify, locName, newValue)	
			
	allData = system.dataset.appendDataset(table1Data, table2Data)
	allData = system.dataset.appendDataset(allData, table3Data)
	allData = system.dataset.appendDataset(allData, table4Data)
	allData = system.dataset.appendDataset(allData, table5Data)
	## filter the required column names 
	## remove columns which is id , date
	## keep only location columns that have valid aliases , so get the day, time and columns of length = locationAliases
	totalLocations = len(self.view.custom.locationAliases)
	
	headers = system.dataset.getColumnHeaders(allData)
#	system.perspective.print(headers)
#	headers = headers[1:(4+totalLocations)] ## 4 index for first 4 columns id, date, day, time
	headers = headers[1:] ###
	
	allData = system.dataset.filterColumns(allData, headers)
	
	newHeaders = []
	selected_cols = [] ###
	for i in range(len(headers)):
		if headers[i] in ['date','Day','TIME']:
			newHeaders.append(headers[i])
			selected_cols.append(headers[i]) ###
		else:
			if headers[i] in self.view.custom.locationAliases:
				newHeaders.append(self.view.custom.locationAliases[headers[i]])
				selected_cols.append(headers[i]) ###

	allData = system.dataset.filterColumns(allData, selected_cols)
	allData.setColumnNames(newHeaders)
	
	## traverse the dataset and construct appropriate event(desc) for each row. The data present in dataset has color etc information which needs to be removed
	for row in range(allData.getRowCount()):
		firstColValue = allData.getValueAt(row,0)
		firstColValue = firstColValue[:10]
		allData = system.dataset.setValue(allData, row, 0, firstColValue)
		for col in range(3, len(newHeaders)): ## first 3 columns are date, day and time, so update data only for location columns from 4th column onwards
			locValue = allData.getValueAt(row,col)
#			system.perspective.print(locValue)
			noteValue = ""
			if locValue is not None and locValue !="":
				if "Note" in locValue: ## check of Notes data is Appenended
					noteValue = " *" + locValue.split(";")[0] + "*"
					locValue = locValue.split(";")[1]
				newLocationValue = ""
				multiEvents = locValue.split(",")
				for i in range(len(multiEvents)):
					splitVal = multiEvents[i].split("-")
					eventName =  multiEvents[i].split("-color")[0].strip()
					eventDesc =  multiEvents[i].split("-desc")[-1].strip()
#					eventName = splitVal[0].strip()
#					eventDesc = splitVal[-1].strip()
					if eventName != "":
						if eventName in eventCategoryDict:
							categoryName = eventCategoryDict[eventName]
						else:
							categoryName = ""
						newLocationValue = newLocationValue + eventName + "-" + categoryName
						if eventDesc != "":
#							newLocationValue = newLocationValue + "(" + eventDesc + ")"
							newLocationValue = newLocationValue
						newLocationValue = newLocationValue + "," ## , separated list if event(desc) if more than one events
				if newLocationValue != "":
					newLocationValue = newLocationValue[:-1]

				newLocationValue = newLocationValue + 	noteValue
				allData = system.dataset.setValue(allData, row, col, newLocationValue)
		
	filename = self.view.custom.reportFileName
	
	exceldata = system.dataset.toExcel(True, allData)
	system.perspective.download(filename, exceldata)
